## JavaScript Standards

- Use ES2020+ syntax: optional chaining, nullish coalescing, dynamic imports
- Use `const` by default; `let` only when reassignment is necessary; never `var`
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use `async/await` over `.then()` chains; always handle rejections
- Use strict equality (`===`) throughout
- Avoid mutating function arguments; return new values instead
- Run `{{LINTER}}` before committing
